{
  "text": "Of the patients who underwent RP, 13% were high risk, 51% were intermediate risk, and 35% were low risk. The percentage in each risk category is consistent with other prostate cancer databases . [CITATION_1] The average prebiopsy PSA in the high-risk category was 13.3 ng/\u03bcL. In a recent study evaluating oncologic outcome in high-risk patients, the prebiopsy PSA was slightly higher at 15.9 ng/\u03bcL. [CITATION_2] This difference may be attributable to aggressive PSA screening and shorter time to surgery caused by in-network care within a managed care system.",
  "citation_candidates": [
